  "profile": {
    "summary": "Mei Lin is a 44-year-old Chinese-Australian entrepreneur and head chef, successfully running 'Lin's Kitchen', a Sichuan restaurant in Newtown, Sydney, for over a decade. Having immigrated from Chongqing in 2003, she has built a strong business, adapting to challenges like COVID-19 by diversifying into meal-kits and cooking classes. Mei is married with two teenage children, Jason and Amy, and is actively involved in the local business community. She balances her professional life with personal interests like bushwalking and growing chillies, and enjoys mahjong with friends.",
